{[showcards W:D5 S:DK,C9]

You are North. The bidding has been as shown.

You lead the \D5; \D3, \D10 and won by West with \DK. West now leads the \C9 from his hand 

Play the \CA.

First ask yourself "Where are the \DA and \DQ?"South doesn't have either one or he would have played it at the first trick. So West has both of them. So with those 3 tricks and the 5 \Hs in dummy West only needs to find one more winner. Assuming he has the \CK, (or why play the suit), if you play low he will find that one more winner whichever high \C he plays.

Next ask yourself "Where is the \SA?"Clearly South <b>DOES</b> have this card; otherwise West has his 9 tricks.

So the way to beat the contract is to go up with your \CA, then play \SK, \SQ and a third \S, hoping South holds \S A x x x.}
[Play "W"]D5

