{[showcards W:CK E:S4,C5,C3 S:H4,CA,C6,C2]

You are North. The bidding has been as shown.

You lead the \CK and continue with the \CJ then \CQ, taken by West's \CA. To trick 4 West plays the \H4. What do you play?

Play the \HQ.

To see why you should play the \HQ, just visualize the result if you play low. West will finesse with dummy's \H8. If South wins his \HJ on this trick there will be 4 good \H tricks in dummy. If South withholds his \HJ then Declarer will have 3 \H winners.

Now visualize the result of playing the \HQ. Whether West takes this trick or not he cannot win more than 2 \Hs.}
