{[showcards W:SJ E:S3,H7,H4 S:S5,HA,H2,C2]

You are South. The bidding has been as shown.

You lead the \SJ, the \SK is played from dummy and holds the trick. Next come dummy's \HK, then another trump to East's \HA.

At trick 4 East plays the \C2 from his hand and you must decide what to play.

Play the \C3 (smoothly).

East has 2 small \Cs and faces a choice of dummy plays in the suit. He must decide whether to play you for the \CA or the \CQ. If you play your \CA you make the decision very easy for him.

When you correctly play your small \C life becomes harder for East. Sometimes he will guess correctly and play dummy's \CK, but other times he will play dummy's \CJ, hoping you have the \CQ.}
[Play "W"]SJ

