[Student "E"]
{[showcards S:SA,C2 W:SK]

You are West. The bidding has been as shown.

East led the \SK, won by North's \SA. North played a small \C to dummy's \CA, then led dummy's \HJ.

What do you play? \HQ or \H4? 

Play the \H4.

Remember that North opened 1\H, so he has 5 of them. With only 3 trumps out he has no intention of finessing. Perhaps he led the \HJ just to tempt you to cover in this situation.

If you play low he will win with one of his high \Hs and then you will have a sure \H winner. Along with the \S winner East has you will defeat the slam.

If you cover the \HJ with your \HQ North will again win with one of his high ones. But now the position will be clear to North and he will return to dummy and play another \H, finessing your \H10. With no trump loser he will make the slam. }
[Play "W"]SK

