{[showcards W:DJ]

You are North. The bidding has been as shown.

You lead the \DJ and dummy's \DA wins the first trick. Declarer pulls trumps with dummy's \SK, then his \SA. He then plays his \DK and follows with \CQ, \CK and \CA, discarding a \H from his hand on the last.

With all that completed West plays the \HA. What do you play?

Play the \HK.

It may look foolish to waste your \HK but look what will happen if you don't. West will follow up with another \H and when you win the \HK you will be forced to play a minor suit. Since both East and West are out of \Ds and \Cs you will be giving them a ruff-sluff and the contract.

But if you dump your \HK under West's \HA look at what's left. West has \H losers and when he plays a \H from either hand South will scoop up two tricks with his \H Q 10.}
[Play "W"]DJ

